RIYADH: Saudi Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Adel Al-Jubeir met Ambassador of Greece to the Kingdom Alexis Konstantopoulos in Riyadh on Thursday. During the meeting, they reviewed the bilateral cooperation between the two countries, and the most prominent issues of common interest. The meeting was attended by the director general of the European department, Sultan bin Khuzaim. In a separate meeting, Al-Jubeir met Egypt’s Ambassador to Saudi Arabia Ahmed Farouk. They likewise reviewed bilateral relations and the most prominent regional and international developments of common interest. On Wednesday, the Saudi minister also met Angolan Ambassador Frederico Manuel dos Santos e Silva Cardoso and Peru’s Ambassador Carlos Rodolfo Zapata Lopez to discuss strengthening bilateral relations.